{"title_page": "Men Who Save the World", "text_new": "{{short description|2014 film}}\n{{EngvarB|date=February 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Men Who Save the World\n| image          = Lelaki_Harapan_Dunia.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Liew Seng Tat]]\n| producer       = Sharon Gan\n| writer         = Liew Seng Tat\n| starring       = {{Plainlist |\n* Wan Hanafi Su\n* Harun Salim Bachik\n* Soffi Jikan\n* Jalil Hamid\n* Azhan Rani\n}}\n| music          = Luka Kuncevic\n| cinematography = Teoh Gay Hian\n| editing        = Patrick Minks<br>Liew Seng Tat\n| distributor    = Everything Films\n| released       = {{Film date|2014|8|11|[[Locarno Film Festival]]|2014|11|27|Malaysia|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 94 minutes\n| country        = Malaysia<br>Netherlands<br>Germany<br>France\n| language       = Malay\n| budget         = RM 2.5 million ($ 750 000)\n}}\n\n'''''Men Who Save the World''''' ({{lang-ms|'''Lelaki Harapan Dunia'''}}) is a 2014 internationally co-produced [[comedy film]] written and directed by [[Liew Seng Tat]]. It is produced by Sharon Gan and is a co-production project between Everything Films Sdn. Bhd. (Malaysia) and Volya Films (The Netherlands), Flying Moon Filmproduktion (Germany) and Mandra Films (France) with support from [[Ministry of Information, Communication and Culture (Malaysia)]], Torino Film Lab (Italy), [[Huub Bals|Hubert Bals Fund]] (The Netherlands), [[Netherlands Film Fund]], [[World Cinema Foundation|World Cinema Fund]] (Germany), Visions Sud Est (Switzerland), Fondation Groupama Gan pour le Cin\u00e9ma \u2013 Cinefondation (France), [[Prince Claus of the Netherlands|Prince Claus]] (The Netherlands), Sundance Institute Mahindra Global Filmmaking Award, Sundance Institute Feature Film Program dan the Doris Duke Foundation (USA).\n\nThe film was selected as the Malaysian entry for the [[Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Best Foreign Language Film]] at the [[88th Academy Awards]] but it was not nominated.<ref name=\"Malaysia\">{{cite web|url=http://www.bernama.com/bernama/v8/ge/newsgeneral.php?id=1174231 |title=Malaysia To Offer Over 1,600 Hours Of Creative Content At MIPCOM 2015 |work=Bernama |date=25 September 2015 |accessdate=25 September 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"MMail\">{{cite web|url=http://www.themalaymailonline.com/showbiz/article/liew-seng-tats-lelaki-harapan-dunia-is-malaysias-pick-as-oscar-entry |title=Liew Seng Tat\u2019s \u2018Lelaki Harapan Dunia\u2019 is Malaysia\u2019s pick as Oscar entry |work=Malay Mail Online |date=25 September 2015 |accessdate=25 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Wan Hanafi Su]] as Pak Awang\n* Soffi Jikan as Wan\n* Jjamal Ahmed as Mat Kacamata\n* [[Harun Salim Bachik]] as Megat\n* Azhan Rani as Cina\n* Muhammad Farhan Mohamad Nizam as Zakari\n* Hazeehan Husain as the Headman's Wife\n* Othman Hafsham as Encik Juta Seri\n* Jalil Hamid as Tok Bilal\n* Azman Hassan as Khamis\n* Khalid Mboyelwa Hussein as Solomon\n* Bob Idris as Mat Lembu\n* [[Hishamuddin Rais]] as the [[Bomoh|Tok Bomoh]]\n\n==Production==\nLiew developed Lelaki Harapan Dunia at the Cannes Director's Residence \u2013 [[Cin\u00e9fondation]] and participated at the 2011 [[Sundance Institute|Sundance Screenwriters Lab]]. The film was shot in [[Kuala Kangsar]], [[Perak]]. Lelaki Harapan Dunia was supposed to be Liew's debut feature film but he ended up shelving it and making ''[[Flower in the Pocket]]'' first. The critical success of Liew's debut paved the way for him to receive grants from all over the world for Lelaki Harapan Dunia.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://poskod.my/features/lelaki-harapan-dunia/|title=Lelaki Harapan Dunia|last=Ho|first=Mabel|date=|year=2014|website=Poskod Malaysia|publisher=PopDigital Sdn Bhd|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\nThe film had its world premiere at the [[Locarno International Film Festival|67th Locarno International Film Festival]] on 6 August 2014. Its North American premier was held at the [[2014 Toronto International Film Festival]] on 4 September 2014. The film was released in [[Malaysia]] on 27 November 2014.\n\n==Critical reception==\nThe film got mixed reviews with praise for the humour and stunning [[cinematography]]. Critics were also more focused on the issue of the absence of [[actresses]],  [[homosexuality]] and [[racism]] that exists in this film. Kamran Ahmed of entertainment portal Nextprojection.com in describing the film,\" It\u2019s an extreme and exaggerated form of humour that works well to make certain ironic or sardonic remarks...\". Shelly Kraicer of film portal Cinema-scope.com reviewed this film as \"... sets out to be a boisterous comedy of rural cross-dressing and ghostly hauntings, but it has fascinating, somewhat disguised undercurrents suggesting something more serious.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cinema-scope.com/cinema-scope-online/tiff-2014-men-save-world-liew-seng-tat-malaysianetherlandsgermanyfrance-contemporary-world-cinema/|title=TIFF 2014 \u2013 Men Who Save the World (Liew Seng Tat, Malaysia/Netherlands/Germany/France) \u2013 Contemporary World Cinema|work=cinema-scope.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nextprojection.com/2014/10/28/viff-class-enemy-men-save-world-gente-de-bien-mercedes-sosa-voice-latin-america-still-life-reviews/|title=VIFF: Class Enemy, Men Who Save the World, Gente de bien, Mercedes Sosa: Voice of Latin America, Still Life Reviews|author=Kamran Ahmed|work=Next Projection}}</ref> Jenna Hossack of dorkshelf.com entertainment portal also provides two words to describe this film, namely \"Vibrant and funny\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dorkshelf.com/2014/09/07/tiff-2014-men-who-save-the-world-review/|title=TIFF 2014: Men Who Save the World Review|work=Dork Shelf}}</ref> Shane Scott-Travis of entertainment portal vivascene.com give 4 out of 5 stars for this movie.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vivascene.com/featured-articles/viff-men-who-save-the-world-film-review/|title='Men Who Save The World' Film Review \u2013 Vivascene|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141001220510/http://vivascene.com/featured-articles/viff-men-who-save-the-world-film-review/|archivedate=1 October 2014}}</ref> Muzaffar Mustafa from [[Astro Awani]] also praised \"... among the best films of in aspects of production, both in terms of art direction and cinematography.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.astroawani.com/news/show/lelaki-harapan-dunia-bila-fitnah-bermaharajalela-satu-kampung-huru-hara-49134?cp|title=Lelaki Harapan Dunia, bila fitnah bermaharajalela, satu kampung huru-hara|last=Muzaffar Mustapa|first=|date=29 November 2014|website=Astro Awani|publisher=Astro Awani Network Sdn Bhd|language=Malay|access-date=1 August 2016}}</ref> Irvan Syed Syed Mahdi of [[Utusan Malaysia]] praised the film directing and cinematography.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.utusan.com.my/hiburan/siapa-lelaki-harapan-dunia-1.30891|title=Siapa Lelaki Harapan Dunia?|last=Syed Mussaddad Syed Mahdi|first=|date=30 November 2014|website=[[Utusan Malaysia|Utusan Online]]|publisher=Utusan Melayu (M) Berhad|language=Malay|access-date=1 August 2016}}</ref> Hassan Abd Al-Muttalib from the same newspaper also commented of the film being \" a continuation of the early Malaysian cinema\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.utusan.com.my/hiburan/filem-malaysia-8232-di-persada-dunia-1.33602|title=Filem Malaysia di persada dunia|last=Hassan Abd Muthalib|first=|date=7 December 2014|website=[[Utusan Malaysia|Utusan Online]]|publisher=Utusan Melayu (M) Berhad|language=Malay|access-date=1 August 2016}}</ref> K. Anand of the news portal [[The Malaysian Insider]] loomed on the film as \"the best local film this year and among the best films of the decade.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.themalaysianinsider.com/opinion/k-anand/article/a-malaysian-movie-to-be-proud-of |title=A Malaysian movie to be proud of |last=K. Anand |date=11 December 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150930110903/http://www.themalaysianinsider.com/opinion/k-anand/article/a-malaysian-movie-to-be-proud-of |archive-date=30 September 2015 |work=The Malaysian Insider |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nJay Weissberg of [[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] criticised the film for playing with issues of [[homosexuality]] and [[racism]]. \"This ultra-light comedy about an apparently haunted house in the jungle is loaded with racially problematic scenes and homophobic gags, plus barely one line is uttered by the marginalized female characters.\" he stated.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/reviews/film-review-men-who-save-the-world-1201282850/|title=\u2018Men Who Save the World\u2019 Review: There\u2019s No Saving This Malaysian Movie|last=Weissberg|first=Jay|date=15 August 2014|publisher=Variety Media, LLC|access-date=1 August 2016|work=Variety}}</ref> Justin Lowe of [[The Hollywood Reporter]] stated, \"From ridiculing superstitious villagers to stereotyping Africans and completely sidelining women, Liew\u2019s film barrels ahead with barely a clue. His puerile script leads the well-known Malaysian cast members pointlessly astray and returns little on the clearly significant effort required to move the house and shoot extensive footage in the depths of the jungle.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/men-who-save-world-toronto-735719|title='Men Who Save The World': Toronto Review|last=Lowe|first=Justin|date=25 September 2014|access-date=1 August 2016|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref>  Mark Adams of Screen Daily questioned the absence of actresses in this film.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.screendaily.com/reviews/the-latest/men-who-save-the-world/5076143.article|title=Men Who Save The World|last=Adams|first=Mark|date=12 August 2014|website=[[ScreenDaily]]|publisher=Media Business Insight Limited|access-date=31 July 2016}}</ref> Nazim Masnawi of news portal [[Malaysiakini]] observes the film imitating the style of [[Mamat Khalid]]'s early films but whereas Mamat \"still gives sympathy to his character line-up\", Liew is \"really brutal with his satire\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.malaysiakini.com/news/282340|title=Lelaki Harapan Dunia jauh dari hati|last=Nazim Masnawi|first=|date=3 December 2014|publisher=Mkini Dot Com Sdn Bhd|language=Malay|access-date=1 August 2016|work=[[Malaysiakini]]}}</ref>   Aidil Rusli of [[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]] notes of this movie as being filled with potential yet that can not be translated properly.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thestar.com.my/Lifestyle/Entertainment/Movies/Reviews/2014/11/29/Lelaki-Harapan-Dunia/|title=Lelaki Harapan Dunia is a breakout delight|last=Aidil Rusli|first=|date=29 November 2014|publisher=Star Media Group Berhad|access-date=31 July 2016|work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star Online]]}}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\nLelaki Harapan Dunia swept five awards among other fourteen categories nominated including the prestigious Best Picture and Best Director awards in 27th Malaysian Film Festival.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Award\n! Category\n! Recipients and nominees\n! Result\n|-\n|[[2014 Toronto International Film Festival]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiewire.com/article/toronto-international-film-festival-reveals-7-big-new-lineups-20140812 |title=TIFF Adds 'Clouds of Sils Maria' and 'Two Days, One Night,' Reveals 5 More Lineups |accessdate=28 August 2014 |work=Indiewire}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hmetro.com.my/node/8902|title=Lelaki Harapan Dunia: Budaya tradisi penuh nostalgia|work=HM Online}}</ref>\n|Contemporary World Cinema & Grolsch Audience Selection Award\n|Sharon Gan\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Vancouver International Film Festival#2014|33rd Vancouver International Film Festival]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://malaysiandigest.com/hiburan/521201-lelaki-harapan-dunia-ke-peringkat-antarabangsa.html|title=Lelaki Harapan Dunia ke Peringkat Antarabangsa|author=farahanim|work=Malaysian Digest}}</ref>\n|Dragons & Tigers\n|Sharon Gan \n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|[[19th Busan International Film Festival]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.murai.com.my/berita/tempatan/article/articleid/358831/nik-amir-nafi-sindir-wartawan-dalam-kil|title=Nik Amir Nafi Sindir Wartawan Dalam KIL|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150928083525/http://www.murai.com.my/berita/tempatan/article/articleid/358831/nik-amir-nafi-sindir-wartawan-dalam-kil|archivedate=28 September 2015}}</ref>\n| A Window On Asian Cinema\n|Sharon Gan\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Locarno International Film Festival|67th Locarno International Film Festival]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.murai.com.my/berita/tempatan/article/articleid/591918/lelaki-harapan-dunia-sertai-festival-filem-antarabangsa-locarno|title=Lelaki Harapan Dunia Sertai Festival Filem Antarabangsa Locarno!|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thesundaily.my/news/1131858|title=Liew Seng Tat's up-lifting film|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://moviemotion.com.my/lelaki-harapan-dunia-world-premiere-at-festival-del-film-locarno/|title=Lelaki Harapan Dunia World Premiere at Festival Del Film Locarno \u2013 Moviemotion|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nst.com.my/node/15934|title=Showbiz: Malaysian film at Festival del Film Locarno|work=NST Online}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.colourlessopinions.com/2014/08/lelaki-harapan-dunia-Festival-Film-Locarno.html|title=\"Lelaki Harapan Dunia\" selected for 67th Festival del Film Locarno|author=Tony Teh|work=ColourlessOpinions.com\u2122}}</ref>\n| Concorso Cineasti del Presente\n|Sharon Gan\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Singapore International Film Festival|25th Singapore International Film Festival]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sgiff.com/films/men-who-save-the-world/|title=Men Who Save The World \u2013 Singapore International Film Festival|work=Singapore International Film Festival|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141126051441/http://sgiff.com/films/men-who-save-the-world/|archivedate=26 November 2014}}</ref>\n|Asian Feature Film\n|Sharon Gan \n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|3rd Nara International Film Festival <ref>{{Cite web |url=http://mediahiburan.karangkraf.com/terkini/lelaki-harapan-dunia-ke-2-festival-filem-antarabangsa-1.315671 |title=Archived copy |access-date=15 November 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141123024714/http://mediahiburan.karangkraf.com/terkini/lelaki-harapan-dunia-ke-2-festival-filem-antarabangsa-1.315671 |archive-date=23 November 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.murai.com.my/berita/tempatan/article/articleid/611347/lelaki-harapan-dunia-tayang-di-2-festival-filem-antarabangsa-bulan-ini|title=Lelaki Harapan Dunia Tayang Di 2 Festival Filem Antarabangsa Bulan Ini|publisher=}}</ref>\n|Main Competition\n|Sharon Gan\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Golden Horse Film Festival and Awards|Golden Horse Film Festival and Awards 2014]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dailyseni.com/index.php/home/news/film-tv/item/1946-lelaki-harapan-dunia-terpilih-ke-festival-filem-taipei-golden-horse|title=Lelaki Harapan Dunia Terpilih ke Festival Filem Taipei Golden Horse|author=The Daily Seni|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://terbakor.com/2014/11/14/lelaki-harapan-dunia-terpilih-ke-festival-filem-golden-horse-taipei/|title=Lelaki Harapan Dunia terpilih ke Festival Filem Golden Horse, Taipei|work=Terbakor !}}</ref>\n|Asian Window\n|Sharon Gan \n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|[[Kolkata International Film Festival]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.budiey.com/lelaki-harapan-dunia-terpilih-ke-festival-filem-antarabangsa-kolkata/|title=Lelaki Harapan Dunia Terpilih Ke Festival Filem Antarabangsa Kolkata|work=Sensasi Selebriti}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tupai.com.my/2014/11/lelaki-harapan-dunia-terpilih-ke.html|title=\"Lelaki Harapan Dunia\" terpilih ke Festival Filem Kolkata|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129022525/http://www.tupai.com.my/2014/11/lelaki-harapan-dunia-terpilih-ke.html|archivedate=29 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wom.my/berita-terkini/lelaki-harapan-dunia/|title=Lelaki Harapan Dunia \u2013 Women Online Magazine|work=Women Online Magazine}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://my.entertainment.yahoo.com/news/lelaki-harapan-dunia-terpilih-ke-festival-filem-kolkata-035300944.html|title=\"Lelaki Harapan Dunia\" terpilih ke Festival Filem Kolkata|date=7 November 2014|work=Yahoo}}</ref>\n|Asian Select (NETPAC Award)\n|Sharon Gan\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|[[International Film Festival Rotterdam|2015 International Film Festival Rotterdam]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.iffr.com/en/films/lelaki-harapan-dunia/|title=Men Who Save the World \u2013 IFFR.COM \u2013 International Film Festival Rotterdam 2015 \u2013 IFFR|work=iffr.com|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150115080751/https://www.iffr.com/en/films/lelaki-harapan-dunia/|archivedate=15 January 2015}}</ref>\n|Bright Future\n|Sharon Gan\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|[[G\u00f6teborg International Film Festival|2015 G\u00f6teborg International Film Festival]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://filmweb01.filmfestival.org/filmfestival/info/en/festivalprogram/programentry?filmId=186911|title=G\u00f6teborg Film Festival|website=filmweb01.filmfestival.org|accessdate=10 May 2017}}</ref>\n|Den gudomliga komedin\n|Sharon Gan\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"13\"| 27th Malaysian Film Festival (FFM) <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cinema.com.my/bm/articles/news_details.aspx?search=2015.n_lelakiharapandunia13nominationsbm_24855&title=-Lelaki-Harapan-Dunia-dapat-13-pencalonan-di-FFM27|title=cinema.com.my: \"Lelaki Harapan Dunia\" dapat 13 pencalonan di FFM27|work=cinema.com.my}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.astroawani.com/entertainment-news/mff27-journey-wins-4-trophies-including-best-director-and-best-actor-72344|title=MFF27: The Journey wins 4 trophies, including Best Director and Best Actor|work=astroawani.com}}</ref>\n| Best Picture\n| Everythings Film Sdn Bhd\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Director\n| Liew Seng Tat\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Actor\n| Wan Hanafi Su\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Screenplay\n| Liew Seng Tat\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Story\n| Liew Seng Tat\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Cinematography\n| Teoh Gay Hian\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Editing\n| Liew Seng Tat\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Sound Editing\n| Imaginax Studios \n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Art Editing\n| Tunku Mohd Taufek \n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Original Score\n| Imaginax Studios\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Costume Design\n| Tunku Mohd Taufek\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Best Child Actor\n| Raykarl Iskandar\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Muhammad Farhan\n| {{nom}} \n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\"|  Kuala Lumpur Film Critics Society Awards 2015 <ref>{{cite web|url=http://tontonfilem.blogspot.my/2015/09/senarai-pencalonan-anugerah-majlis.html|title=TONTONFILEM|work=blogspot.my}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ampfkl.blogspot.my/2015/10/keputusan-anugerah-majlis-pengkritik.html |title=Men Who Save the World}}</ref> \n| Best Picture\n| Everythings Film Sdn Bhd\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Director\n| Liew Seng Tat\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Actor\n| Wan Hanafi Su\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Screenplay\n| Liew Seng Tat\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Cinematography\n| Teoh Gay Hian\n| {{won}}\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of submissions to the 88th Academy Awards for Best Foreign Language Film]]\n* [[List of Malaysian submissions for the Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|3797880|Men Who Save the World}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20160504073300/http://lhd.everythingfilms.net/en/ Official website]\n* [https://www.facebook.com/lelakiharapandunia Official Facebook page]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Men Who Save The World}}\n[[Category:2014 films]]\n[[Category:2010s comedy films]]\n[[Category:Malaysian films]]\n[[Category:Malaysian comedy films]]\n[[Category:Dutch films]]\n[[Category:Dutch comedy films]]\n[[Category:German films]]\n[[Category:German comedy films]]\n[[Category:French films]]\n[[Category:French comedy films]]\n[[Category:Malay-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Liew Seng Tat]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Liew Seng Tat]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2014 film}}\n{{EngvarB|date=February 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Men Who Save the World\n| image          = Lelaki_Harapan_Dunia.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Liew Seng Tat]]\n| producer       = Sharon Gan\n| writer         = Liew Seng Tat\n| starring       = {{Plainlist |\n* Wan Hanafi Su\n* Harun Salim Bachik\n* Soffi Jikan\n* Jalil Hamid\n* Azhan Rani\n}}\n| music          = Luka Kuncevic\n| cinematography = Teoh Gay Hian\n| editing        = Patrick Minks<br>Liew Seng Tat\n| distributor    = Everything Films\n| released       = {{Film date|2014|8|11|[[Locarno Film Festival]]|2014|11|27|Malaysia|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 94 minutes\n| country        = Malaysia<br>Netherlands<br>Germany<br>France\n| language       = Malay\n| budget         = RM 2.5 million ($ 750 000)\n}}\n\n'''''Men Who Save the World''''' ({{lang-ms|'''Lelaki Harapan Dunia'''}}) is a 2014 internationally co-produced [[comedy film]] written and directed by [[Liew Seng Tat]]. It is produced by Sharon Gan and is a co-production project between Everything Films Sdn. Bhd. (Malaysia) and Volya Films (The Netherlands), Flying Moon Filmproduktion (Germany) and Mandra Films (France) with support from [[Ministry of Information, Communication and Culture (Malaysia)]], Torino Film Lab (Italy), [[Huub Bals|Hubert Bals Fund]] (The Netherlands), [[Netherlands Film Fund]], [[World Cinema Foundation|World Cinema Fund]] (Germany), Visions Sud Est (Switzerland), Fondation Groupama Gan pour le Cin\u00e9ma \u2013 Cinefondation (France), [[Prince Claus of the Netherlands|Prince Claus]] (The Netherlands), Sundance Institute Mahindra Global Filmmaking Award, Sundance Institute Feature Film Program dan the Doris Duke Foundation (USA).\n\nThe film was selected as the Malaysian entry for the [[Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Best Foreign Language Film]] at the [[88th Academy Awards]] but it was not nominated.<ref name=\"Malaysia\">{{cite web|url=http://www.bernama.com/bernama/v8/ge/newsgeneral.php?id=1174231 |title=Malaysia To Offer Over 1,600 Hours Of Creative Content At MIPCOM 2015 |work=Bernama |date=25 September 2015 |accessdate=25 September 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"MMail\">{{cite web|url=http://www.themalaymailonline.com/showbiz/article/liew-seng-tats-lelaki-harapan-dunia-is-malaysias-pick-as-oscar-entry |title=Liew Seng Tat\u2019s \u2018Lelaki Harapan Dunia\u2019 is Malaysia\u2019s pick as Oscar entry |work=Malay Mail Online |date=25 September 2015 |accessdate=25 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Wan Hanafi Su]] as Pak Awang\n* Soffi Jikan as Wan\n* Jjamal Ahmed as Mat Kacamata\n* [[Harun Salim Bachik]] as Megat\n* Azhan Rani as Cina\n* Muhammad Farhan Mohamad Nizam as Zakari\n* Hazeehan Husain as the Headman's Wife\n* Othman Hafsham as Encik Juta Seri\n* Jalil Hamid as Tok Bilal\n* Azman Hassan as Khamis\n* Khalid Mboyelwa Hussein as Solomon\n* Bob Idris as Mat Lembu\n* [[Hishamuddin Rais]] as the [[Bomoh|Tok Bomoh]]\n\n==Production==\nLiew developed Lelaki Harapan Dunia at the Cannes Director's Residence \u2013 [[Cin\u00e9fondation]] and participated at the 2011 [[Sundance Institute|Sundance Screenwriters Lab]]. The film was shot in [[Kuala Kangsar]], [[Perak]]. Lelaki Harapan Dunia was supposed to be Liew's debut feature film but he ended up shelving it and making ''[[Flower in the Pocket]]'' first. The critical success of Liew's debut paved the way for him to receive grants from all over the world for Lelaki Harapan Dunia.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://poskod.my/features/lelaki-harapan-dunia/|title=Lelaki Harapan Dunia|last=Ho|first=Mabel|date=|year=2014|website=Poskod Malaysia|publisher=PopDigital Sdn Bhd|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\nThe film had its world premiere at the [[Locarno International Film Festival|67th Locarno International Film Festival]] on 6 August 2014. Its North American premier was held at the [[2014 Toronto International Film Festival]] on 4 September 2014. The film was released in [[Malaysia]] on 27 November 2014.\n\n==Critical reception==\nThe film got mixed reviews with praise for the humour and stunning [[cinematography]]. Critics were also more focused on the issue of the absence of [[actresses]],  [[homosexuality]] and [[racism]] that exists in this film. Kamran Ahmed of entertainment portal Nextprojection.com in describing the film,\" It\u2019s an extreme and exaggerated form of humour that works well to make certain ironic or sardonic remarks...\". Shelly Kraicer of film portal Cinema-scope.com reviewed this film as \"... sets out to be a boisterous comedy of rural cross-dressing and ghostly hauntings, but it has fascinating, somewhat disguised undercurrents suggesting something more serious.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cinema-scope.com/cinema-scope-online/tiff-2014-men-save-world-liew-seng-tat-malaysianetherlandsgermanyfrance-contemporary-world-cinema/|title=TIFF 2014 \u2013 Men Who Save the World (Liew Seng Tat, Malaysia/Netherlands/Germany/France) \u2013 Contemporary World Cinema|work=cinema-scope.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nextprojection.com/2014/10/28/viff-class-enemy-men-save-world-gente-de-bien-mercedes-sosa-voice-latin-america-still-life-reviews/|title=VIFF: Class Enemy, Men Who Save the World, Gente de bien, Mercedes Sosa: Voice of Latin America, Still Life Reviews|author=Kamran Ahmed|work=Next Projection}}</ref> Jenna Hossack of dorkshelf.com entertainment portal also provides two words to describe this film, namely \"Vibrant and funny\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dorkshelf.com/2014/09/07/tiff-2014-men-who-save-the-world-review/|title=TIFF 2014: Men Who Save the World Review|work=Dork Shelf}}</ref> Shane Scott-Travis of entertainment portal vivascene.com give 4 out of 5 stars for this movie.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vivascene.com/featured-articles/viff-men-who-save-the-world-film-review/|title='Men Who Save The World' Film Review \u2013 Vivascene|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141001220510/http://vivascene.com/featured-articles/viff-men-who-save-the-world-film-review/|archivedate=1 October 2014}}</ref> Muzaffar Mustafa from [[Astro Awani]] also praised \"... among the best films of in aspects of production, both in terms of art direction and cinematography.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.astroawani.com/news/show/lelaki-harapan-dunia-bila-fitnah-bermaharajalela-satu-kampung-huru-hara-49134?cp|title=Lelaki Harapan Dunia, bila fitnah bermaharajalela, satu kampung huru-hara|last=Muzaffar Mustapa|first=|date=29 November 2014|website=Astro Awani|publisher=Astro Awani Network Sdn Bhd|language=Malay|access-date=1 August 2016}}</ref> Irvan Syed Syed Mahdi of [[Utusan Malaysia]] praised the film directing and cinematography.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.utusan.com.my/hiburan/siapa-lelaki-harapan-dunia-1.30891|title=Siapa Lelaki Harapan Dunia?|last=Syed Mussaddad Syed Mahdi|first=|date=30 November 2014|website=[[Utusan Malaysia|Utusan Online]]|publisher=Utusan Melayu (M) Berhad|language=Malay|access-date=1 August 2016}}</ref> Hassan Abd Al-Muttalib from the same newspaper also commented of the film being \" a continuation of the early Malaysian cinema\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.utusan.com.my/hiburan/filem-malaysia-8232-di-persada-dunia-1.33602|title=Filem Malaysia di persada dunia|last=Hassan Abd Muthalib|first=|date=7 December 2014|website=[[Utusan Malaysia|Utusan Online]]|publisher=Utusan Melayu (M) Berhad|language=Malay|access-date=1 August 2016}}</ref> K. Anand of the news portal [[The Malaysian Insider]] loomed on the film as \"the best local film this year and among the best films of the decade.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.themalaysianinsider.com/opinion/k-anand/article/a-malaysian-movie-to-be-proud-of |title=A Malaysian movie to be proud of |last=K. Anand |date=11 December 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150930110903/http://www.themalaysianinsider.com/opinion/k-anand/article/a-malaysian-movie-to-be-proud-of |archive-date=30 September 2015 |work=The Malaysian Insider |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nJay Weissberg of [[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] criticised the film for playing with issues of [[homosexuality]] and [[racism]]. \"This ultra-light comedy about an apparently haunted house in the jungle is loaded with racially problematic scenes and homophobic gags, plus barely one line is uttered by the marginalized female characters.\" he stated.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/reviews/film-review-men-who-save-the-world-1201282850/|title=\u2018Men Who Save the World\u2019 Review: There\u2019s No Saving This Malaysian Movie|last=Weissberg|first=Jay|date=15 August 2014|publisher=Variety Media, LLC|access-date=1 August 2016|work=Variety}}</ref> Justin Lowe of [[The Hollywood Reporter]] stated, \"From ridiculing superstitious villagers to stereotyping Africans and completely sidelining women, Liew\u2019s film barrels ahead with barely a clue. His puerile script leads the well-known Malaysian cast members pointlessly astray and returns little on the clearly significant effort required to move the house and shoot extensive footage in the depths of the jungle.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/men-who-save-world-toronto-735719|title='Men Who Save The World': Toronto Review|last=Lowe|first=Justin|date=25 September 2014|access-date=1 August 2016|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref>  Mark Adams of Screen Daily questioned the absence of actresses in this film.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.screendaily.com/reviews/the-latest/men-who-save-the-world/5076143.article|title=Men Who Save The World|last=Adams|first=Mark|date=12 August 2014|website=[[ScreenDaily]]|publisher=Media Business Insight Limited|access-date=31 July 2016}}</ref> Nazim Masnawi of news portal [[Malaysiakini]] observes the film imitating the style of [[Mamat Khalid]]'s early films but whereas Mamat \"still gives sympathy to his character line-up\", Liew is \"really brutal with his satire\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.malaysiakini.com/news/282340|title=Lelaki Harapan Dunia jauh dari hati|last=Nazim Masnawi|first=|date=3 December 2014|publisher=Mkini Dot Com Sdn Bhd|language=Malay|access-date=1 August 2016|work=[[Malaysiakini]]}}</ref>   Aidil Rusli of [[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]] notes of this movie as being filled with potential yet that can not be translated properly.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thestar.com.my/Lifestyle/Entertainment/Movies/Reviews/2014/11/29/Lelaki-Harapan-Dunia/|title=Lelaki Harapan Dunia is a breakout delight|last=Aidil Rusli|first=|date=29 November 2014|publisher=Star Media Group Berhad|access-date=31 July 2016|work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star Online]]}}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\nLelaki Harapan Dunia swept five awards among other fourteen categories nominated including the prestigious Best Picture and Best Director awards in 27th Malaysian Film Festival.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Award\n! Category\n! Recipients and nominees\n! Result\n|-\n|[[2014 Toronto International Film Festival]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiewire.com/article/toronto-international-film-festival-reveals-7-big-new-lineups-20140812 |title=TIFF Adds 'Clouds of Sils Maria' and 'Two Days, One Night,' Reveals 5 More Lineups |accessdate=28 August 2014 |work=Indiewire}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hmetro.com.my/node/8902|title=Lelaki Harapan Dunia: Budaya tradisi penuh nostalgia|work=HM Online}}</ref>\n|Contemporary World Cinema & Grolsch Audience Selection Award\n|Sharon Gan\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Vancouver International Film Festival#2014|33rd Vancouver International Film Festival]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://malaysiandigest.com/hiburan/521201-lelaki-harapan-dunia-ke-peringkat-antarabangsa.html|title=Lelaki Harapan Dunia ke Peringkat A