{"title_page": "Men Against the Arctic", "text_new": "{{short description|1955 film}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Men Against the Arctic\n| image          =\n| caption        =\n| director       = [[Winston Hibler]]\n| producer       = [[Walt Disney]]<br>[[Ben Sharpsteen]]\n| writer         = Winston Hibler\n| narrator       = Winston Hibler\n| starring       = Winston Hibler\n| music          = [[Oliver Wallace]]\n| cinematography = William Fortin<br>Elmo G. Jones\n| editing        = Grant K. Smith\n| studio         = [[The Walt Disney Company|Walt Disney Productions]]\n| distributor    = [[Walt Disney Studios Motion Pictures|Buena Vista Distribution Co. Inc.]]\n| released       = {{Film date|1955|12|21}}\n| runtime        = 30 minutes\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n}}\n\n'''''Men Against the Arctic''''' is a 1955 American [[short film|short]] [[documentary film]] directed by [[Winston Hibler]]. It was part of Disney's [[People & Places]] series. It won an [[Academy Awards|Oscar]] at the [[28th Academy Awards]] in 1956 for [[Academy Award for Best Documentary (Short Subject)|Documentary Short Subject]].<ref name=\"NY Times\">{{cite web |url=https://movies.nytimes.com/movie/300255/Men-Against-The-Arctic/details |title=New York Times: Men Against the Arctic |accessdate=May 26, 2008 |work=NY Times |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110520033735/http://movies.nytimes.com/movie/300255/Men-Against-The-Arctic/details |archive-date=May 20, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=\"Oscars1956\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/1956 |title=The 28th Academy Awards (1956) Nominees and Winners |accessdate=May 31, 2019 |publisher=Oscars.org ([[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]])}}</ref> It was also entered into the [[6th Berlin International Film Festival]].<ref name=\"Berlinale 1956\">{{cite web |url=http://www.berlinale.de/en/archiv/jahresarchive/1956/02_programm_1956/02_Programm_1956.html |title=6th Berlin International Film Festival: In Competition |accessdate=December 26, 2009 |work=berlinale.de}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Winston Hibler]] as Narrator (voice)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://ftvdb.bfi.org.uk/sift/title/280202 BFI description of the documentary]\n*{{IMDb title|id=0048369|title=Men Against the Arctic}}\n\n{{Academy Award Best Documentary Short |state=collapsed}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Men Against The Arctic}}\n[[Category:1955 films]]\n[[Category:1950s short films]]\n[[Category:1950s documentary films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Short documentary films]]\n[[Category:American documentary films]]\n[[Category:Best Documentary Short Subject Academy Award winners]]\n[[Category:Disney documentary films]]\n[[Category:Documentary films about the Arctic]]\n[[Category:Films produced by Ben Sharpsteen]]\n[[Category:Films produced by Walt Disney]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Oliver Wallace]]\n[[Category:Disney short films]]\n{{short-documentary-film-stub}}\n{{arctic-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1955 film}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2018}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Men Against the Arctic\n| image          =\n| caption        =\n| director       = [[Winston Hibler]]\n| producer       = [[Walt Disney]]<br>[[Ben Sharpsteen]]\n| writer         = Winston Hibler\n| narrator       = Winston Hibler\n| starring       = Winston Hibler\n| music          = [[Oliver Wallace]]\n| cinematography = William Fortin<br>Elmo G. Jones\n| editing        = Grant K. Smith\n| studio         = [[The Walt Disney Company|Walt Disney Productions]]\n| distributor    = [[Walt Disney Studios Motion Pictures|Buena Vista Distribution Co. Inc.]]\n| released       = {{Film date|1955|12|21}}\n| runtime        = 30 minutes\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n}}\n\n'''''Men Against the Arctic''''' is a 1955 American [[short film|short]] [[documentary film]] directed by [[Winston Hibler]]. It was part of Disney's [[People & Places]] series. It won an [[Academy Awards|Oscar]] at the [[28th Academy Awards]] in 1956 for [[Academy Award for Best Documentary (Short Subject)|Documentary Short Subject]].<ref name=\"NY Times\">{{cite web |url=https://movies.nytimes.com/movie/300255/Men-Against-The-Arctic/details |title=New York Times: Men Against the Arctic |accessdate=May 26, 2008 |work=NY Times |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110520033735/http://movies.nytimes.com/movie/300255/Men-Against-The-Arctic/details |archive-date=May 20, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=\"Oscars1956\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/1956 |title=The 28th Academy Awards (1956) Nominees and Winners |accessdate=May 31, 2019 |publisher=Oscars.org ([[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]])}}</ref> It was also entered into the [[6th Berlin International Film Festival]].<ref name=\"Berlinale 1956\">{{cite web |url=http://www.berlinale.de/en/archiv/jahresarchive/1956/02_programm_1956/02_Programm_1956.html |title=6th Berlin International Film Festival: In Competition |accessdate=December 26, 2009 |work=berlinale.de}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Winston Hibler]] as Narrator (voice)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://ftvdb.bfi.org.uk/sift/title/280202 BFI description of the documentary]\n*{{IMDb title|id=0048369|title=Men Against the Arctic}}\n\n{{Academy Award Best Documentary Short |state=collapsed}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Men Against The Arctic}}\n[[Category:1955 films]]\n[[Category:1950s short films]]\n[[Category:1950s documentary films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Short documentary films]]\n[[Category:American documentary films]]\n[[Category:Best Documentary Short Subject Academy Award winners]]\n[[Category:Disney documentary films]]\n[[Category:Documentary films about the Arctic]]\n[[Category:Films produced by Ben Sharpsteen]]\n[[Category:Films produced by Walt Disney]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Oliver Wallace]]\n[[Category:Disney short films]]\n{{short-documentary-film-stub}}\n{{arctic-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lugnuts", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Men_Against_the_Arctic"}
